The paper presents a deep reinforcement learning algorithm for robot behavior learning, which involves both exploration and planning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also focuses on robot behavior learning, which suggests that it could belong to cs.RO (Robotics). The algorithm uses deep neural networks, which is a common technique in cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also deals with uncertainty and multi-agent systems, which could fall under cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper evaluates the algorithm on different scenarios, including a human-robot handover, which could be related to cs.CV (Computer Vision).
